President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of Idaho following a severe storm and straight-line winds that occurred on November 17, 2015. This declaration allows federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected area. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Thomas J. Dargan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.